{
  "id": "019d4153-b778-7df0-966f-52ae1a126327",
  "content": "# Multi-Channel RAG: Per-Memory-Type HNSW Indexes -- Design Decisions (2026-03-31)\n\n## What\nSplit LiteStore's single monolithic HNSW index into per-memory-type indexes (Structural, Decisional, Episodic, Analytical, Procedural). Add a MultiChannelSearcher to the composable pipeline that runs per-type retrieval strategies in parallel and fuses via RRF.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Approach A: HashMap-based multi-index.** `LiteStore` replaces single `hnsw: Arc<ArcSwap<Hnsw>>` with `HashMap<MemoryType, Arc<ArcSwap<Hnsw>>>`. MemoryType implements Hash+Eq. HashMap cleanly handles \"for each memory type\" loops without 5x code duplication. Runtime cost of HashMap lookup on 5 entries is negligible.\n\n2. **Backward-compatible search (D1).** Existing `QueryableStore::search()` signature searches ALL indexes (union). A new `search_by_memory_type()` method enables targeted single-type search. No existing callers break.\n\n3. **Separate HNSW ID spaces per type (D2).** Each memory type gets its own counter. Redb mapping tables use prefixed keys (e.g., `\"structural:42\"` in the existing HNSW_TO_UUID table). Simpler than 10 new tables.\n\n4. **Per-type persistence files (D3).** `litestore.hnsw.structural.{graph,data}`, etc. Blue-green rebuild swaps all 5 atomically. Old single-file format triggers auto-rebuild migration on first startup.\n\n5. **MultiChannelSearcher as pipeline Searcher (D4).** Registered in PipelineRegistry as `\"multichannel\"`. Internally runs per-type searchers with configurable strategies per channel. Fuses results via existing RRF fusion.\n\n6. **Channel strategies from config (D5).** New `[rag.pipeline.channels]` config section maps memory types to retrieval strategies:\n   - structural = \"bm25\" (keyword/exact match, code signatures)\n   - decisional = \"vector+graph\" (graph-heavy, decisions are connected)\n   - episodic = \"vector\" (recency-weighted via tier weighting)\n   - analytical = \"vector\" (confidence reranking)\n   - procedural = \"vector\" (access-frequency boost)\n\n7. **PostgresStore unchanged (D6).** PostgresStore uses SQL WHERE clauses. Adding `WHERE memory_type = $1` is trivial and deferred to a fast follow. This change focuses on LiteStore.\n\n## Prerequisites (all met)\n- memory_type field on KnowledgeEntry: EXISTS (5 variants: Structural, Decisional, Episodic, Analytical, Procedural)\n- Access tracking (access_count, last_accessed): EXISTS\n- Tier lifecycle (Hot/Warm/Cold/Forgotten, retention scoring): EXISTS\n- Composable pipeline with RRF fusion: EXISTS (pipeline.rs with Searcher/Fusion/Expander/Reranker traits)\n- content_role to memory_type mapping: EXISTS (code->Structural, decision/design/plan->Decisional, etc.)\n\n## Scope of Changes\n- LiteStore struct: hnsw -> HashMap<MemoryType, ...>, per-type counters\n- LiteStore::open(): Load 5 indexes from disk\n- LiteStore::insert(): Route to correct HNSW by entry.memory_type\n- LiteStore::search(): Union search across all 5 indexes\n- LiteStore::search_by_memory_type(): New targeted single-type search\n- LiteStore::rebuild_from_files(): Build 5 indexes, atomic swap all\n- LiteStore::flush_hnsw(): Persist 5 files\n- Redb tables: Prefixed keys in HNSW_TO_UUID / UUID_TO_HNSW\n- QueryableStore trait: Add search_by_memory_type() with default impl\n- pipeline/searcher.rs: New MemoryTypeSearcher\n- pipeline/registry.rs: Register \"multichannel\" searcher\n- config.rs: Add channel config\n- Migration: Existing single-index users auto-rebuild on first startup\n\n## Alternatives Rejected\n- Approach B (fixed 5-field struct): More verbose, 5x code duplication, no advantage over HashMap for 5 entries\n- Per-type Redb tables (10 new tables): Over-engineering. Prefixed keys in existing tables are simpler and maintain a single transaction scope.\n- Modifying QueryableStore::search() signature: Would break all callers. Adding a new method with default impl is backward-compatible.\n\n## References\n- Issue: chunzhe10/corvia#13\n- Hindsight TEMPR: 4-channel parallel retrieval with RRF fusion (91.4% LongMemEval)\n- Existing pipeline infrastructure: pipeline.rs (Searcher, Fusion, Expander, Reranker traits)",
  "source_version": "mcp",
